What you need to know:

For the WRC commercial rights holder, WRC Promoter, 2020 has been a challenging year after seven of the 14 rounds were cancelled due to the virus and political upheaval in ChileThe man to beat is Briton Elfyn Evans, winner in Turkey, who is looking forward to extending his 18 points lead over Toyota Gazoo Racing teammate Sebastien OgierDefending Sardinia champion Dani Sordo, who claimed the second win of his WRC career on the very last stage in Sardinia last year, completes the Hyundai Motorsport line-up for this event